Key Match Events: The match was washed out without a ball being bowled due to persistent afternoon rain
Pre-Game Insights: England would have been all-but out of the tournament had they lost to Ashes rivals Australia
England captain Jos Buttler said: “The umpires had some big concerns and rightly so because the outfield was very wet and there were some areas in the 30-yard circle that were not fit to play.
Post-Match Reflections: England captain Jos Buttler said: “We are still in the competition and know, to a certain degree, we have our destiny in our own hands,”
Australia captain Aaron Finch said: “First and foremost we’ve got to try and win our remaining games and have to earn the right to push for net run-rate.”
Miscellaneous Highlights: The La Nina weather pattern has caused serious flooding in parts of Victoria
There have now been four matches in the tournament to finish without a result because of the weather
Others: England next play New Zealand on Tuesday in Brisbane before meeting Sri Lanka in Sydney on Saturday 5 November
